  "text": "The Northeast state of Tamaulipas exhibits a high peak of occurrence of TB with regarding at Mexican rate and the frequency of this disease has remained stable during the last 10 years [CITATION_1] . Besides, this region is a natural corridor for exporting of cattle between Mexico and EE.UU. Therefore, both countries have commitment to keep safe their borders [CITATION_2] . Among the factors that may partially explain it, the high migrations rate reported in this region with people from other Mexican states (mainly www.intechopen.com Veracruz, Coahuila, Mexico city, among others) and other Central America countries (i.e. Guatemala, Honduras, among others).",
